The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Friday, August 22, 2003  Timeout
				 																DRAMA				 																																	 August 22 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.30 pm: Sansriti presents Winkle Twinkle. Directed by Debesh Chattopadhyay.				 																																	 August 22 at Madhusudan Mancha; 6.30 pm: Blind Opera presents Rabindranath Tagores Raja. Direction: Subhasish Gangopadhyay.				 																MUSIC				 																																	 August 22 at Rabindra Sadan; 6 pm: Kalabhrit celebrates its 10th anniversary with a cultural programme Anandataranga Jaago.				 																																	 August 22 at St Pauls Cathedral; 6.30 pm: Calcutta Foundation presents an evening of Western classical music by the Calcutta Foundation orchestra, to be conducted by Ethan Chessin.				 																Art				 																																	 Till August 30 at Galerie 88 (except Sunday); 3 pm - 7 pm: The grand old man of Indian art, Chhabidas (M.F. Husain) celebrates his 88th birthday with Four Suites of paintings comprising 88 Husains in oils 003. 				 																																	 Till August 30 at Chitrakoot Art Gallery; 3 pm - 8 pm: An xhibition of paintings on Shree Krishna titled Muraliya Bajere Jamuna Ke Teer featuring paintings of Early Bengal School as well as Jamini Roy, Ramananda bandopadhyay and Subroto Gangopadhyay.				 																																	 Till August 31 (except Monday) at Birla Academy of Art amp; Culture; 4 pm - 8 pm: Young Faces in Contemporary Indian Art features the works of a host of upcoming artists from different parts of the country.				 																																	 Till August 31 at Vikalp Art Shop, Swabhumi; 4 pm - 8 pm: An exhibition of paintings titled Masters Strokes, featuring the works of four renowned artists: K.G. Subramanyan, Shyamal Dutta Roy, Suhas Roy and Sunil Das.				 																																	 August 23 - September 1 at Artists Circle, 46, Circus Avenue; 11 am - 7 pm: An exhibition of paintings titled, Pentamiral, features the works of Biswarup Gharai, Abhijit Dutta, Debasish Das, Samir Roy and Kushal Mukherjee.				 																																	 Till September 30 at Idiyas Gallery, 15 Dover Road; 10.30 am - 7.30 pm: An exhibition of contemporary Indian art and sculptures in various media titled Continuity features the works of a host of upcoming and established artists and sculptors including Anandita, Apto Bhattacharya, Bimal Kundu, Partho Bhattacharjee, Pradeep Rakshit, Prokash Karmakar, Pranab Fauzdar, Sanatan Dinda, Shuvaprasanna, Shyamal Mukherjee, Subroto Das, Suhas Roy and Wasim Kapur.				 																kids corner				 																																	 August 22 at Sasha, 27 Mirza Ghalib Street; 5 pm: Sasha hosts a Crafts Week for children till August 26. This evening, veteran artist Shuvaprasanna will inaugurate the pottery-making session for children. Seasoned craftspeople will be present at the premises with a potters wheel and clay to guide the children. On display will be toys made of glazed terracotta. Folk music, story telling, toy exhibition and other events are on the cards.				 																poetry festival				 																																	 August 28 at Srijan Rooftop, 176 Sarat Bose Road: For promising poets below the age of 25, writing in English, Bengali, Hindi/ Urdu, can participate in Srijans Youth Poetry Festival. Interested candidates have to ubmit at least five of their poems, with their names, dates of birth, address and phone number to the festival coordinator Vikram Pakrashi at vik_ram5rediffmail.com or to language co-ordinators: Boudhayan (2481-1100 for English), Ananya (9830278041 for Bengali) and Awadhesh (2439-7110, for Hindi/ Urdu)				 																meet				 																																	 August 22 at Sandre Hall; 6. 30 pm: Ajoy Ray will present The Genius of Miles Davis. Hosted by The Calcutta School of Music, Jazz Listeners Forum. 				 																PHOTOGRAPHS				 																																	 Till August 27 at Oxford Bookstore; 10 am - 9 pm: An exhibition of photographs by Nilanjan Ray titled Varanasi  An Eternal City. 				 																film festival				 																																	 August 22 at Uttam Mancha: Cine Centrals Japanese Film Festival concludes with the screening of Sleeping Man (dir: Kohei Oguri) (at 4 pm); Duo (dir: Nobuhiro Suwa) (5.45 pm) and Adrenalin Drive (dir: Yaguchi Shinobu).(7.15 pm)				 																fashion SHOW				 																																	 August 22 at ITC Sonar Bangla Sheraton; 6.30 pm: The National Institute of Fashion Design (NIFD), Lindsay Street, hosts its annual event Tomorrow Makers 2003, the graduation show for passing out students. Choreographed by Marc Robinson, a select group of reputed models will showcase the creations in 30 sequences.				 																exhibition				 																																	 Till August 24 at 255 Jodhpur Park; 11 am - 7.30 pm: Nupurs Boutique hosts an exhibition of Madhubani painted sarees, kurtas, dupattas and applique sarees.				 																workshop				 																																	 Till August 26 at Aikataan, IA-290 Salt Lake; 10 am - 5 pm: EZCC holds a workshop on Thangta, to be conducted by Ranjeet Chingtham. Details at 23356796.				 																festival				 																																	 August 22 at Sri Thyagaraja Hall, P-530, Raja Basanta Roy Road; 7 am - 12 noon amp; 6 pm - 9 pm: Sri Maha Chandi Homam begins with Veda Prarthana and concludes with Poornahoothi.				 																cookery				 																																	 August 22 at Jyotirmoy Club, 37/1A, Garcha Road; 3 pm - 5 pm: Red Hot Chilli Pepper hosts a cookery class. Details: Shruti (98300 50814).
